<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>38-112</num>
  <heading>Masculine pronoun to include both male and female.</heading>
  <text>Wherever the masculine pronoun occurs in this chapter it shall be construed to apply to either male or female teachers or employees of the Board of Education.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annoGroup>
      <heading>History</heading>
      <annotation>June 20, 1906, 34 Stat. 321, ch. 3446, § 12</annotation>
      <annotation doc="Pub. L. 90-292">Apr. 22, 1968, 82 Stat. 102, Pub. L. 90-292, § 3(d)</annotation>
    </annoGroup>
    <annoGroup>
      <heading>Prior Codifications</heading>
      <annotation>1981 Ed., § 31-116.</annotation>
      <annotation>1973 Ed., § 31-117.</annotation>
    </annoGroup>
  </annotations>
</section>
